'''Julia Lorilard Wampage Pell''' (1954-2006) was an advocate for the rights of [[same-sex couple]]s and president of the Rhode Alliance for Lesbian and Gay Civil Rights.<ref name="Projo"/> She was born in [[Washington DC]], the youngest child of Nuala Pell and [[Claiborne Pell]], a six-term [[United States Senator]] from [[Rhode Island]].<ref name="Projo">http://www.projo.com/digitalbulletin/content/projo-20060414-jpell.35756a19.html</ref>

Her name "[[Chief Wampage|Wampage]]" derived from her ancestor, the Chief of the [[Siwanoy|Siwanois]] Indians in [[Westchester County, New York|Westchester County]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2009}}

